<TITLE> ACC asked to report on 34 NBR officials for promotion </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 15 (bdnews24.com)  The finance ministry has sought reports from the Anticorruption Commission for promotion of 34 National Board of Revenue officials, a senior government official said Wednesday. The Internal Resources Division of the ministry copied the NBR chairman on a letter, signed by the finance ministry's senior assistant secretary Mafizul Islam. The promotion and selection grade of the 34 NBR officials of Dhaka, Chittagong and Khulna would require updated reports from the ACC, according to the letter. The IRD asked the ACC to let it know if it had any allegations of graft against the officials. bdnews24.
